This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and word embeddings. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a novel framework for learning word embeddings. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as word embeddings are often used in information retrieval tasks. It could also be classified under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as word embeddings are a popular technique in AI research. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision) as word embeddings are also used in image captioning and other computer vision tasks.
